Aaron Gunn is a new MP and right-wing media personality known for viral videos opposing the Great Bear Sea MPA and attacking federal marine policies. In his 2023 video "No Fishing Allowed," he accused MPAs of being unscientific and economically devastating, while omitting Indigenous and scientific perspectives.
Gunn is active on X (Twitter) and YouTube, with a large following for his Conservative commentary. Notoriously, he was disqualified from a 2021 BC Liberal leadership contest after tweets dismissing "gender diversity" and "systemic racism" as myths. These posts, obtained from archives, underscore a willingness to espouse inflammatory, divisive views online. His social channels frequently praise Pierre Poilievre and attack Liberals.
He co-founded Common Sense BC (aligned with Poilievre's federal movement) and worked with billionaire-funded networks (Pacific Prosperity) to elect like-minded politicians. Gunn's alliances include far-right media personalities and activists; he is celebrated by anti-harm-reduction groups. These connections may be used to portray him as influenced by fringe donors and ideologues.
